race.description: Wallamba River Pony Club Maiden Plate
race.comment: Strong Maiden with plenty of chances. SMASHING NOVA (5) improving with racing and should get the right tempo to finish over the top of these. Covered ground from the outside gate with a fighting second over 1250m at this track. A repeat performance can see him secure his first win. PARFUMIER (10) resumes and having her first run for the Darren Treacy yard. Struggled in her last three runs on the provincial circuit and back without a trial. Lugging bit comes off and has sprinted well fresh in the past. Well placed in this company. RUBINSKY (7) handy mare who stretches out to this trip for the first time. Sat on the fast tempo when showing a ton of grit to run second over 1100m at Armidale. Can measure up again from the good gate. KIRKALL (4) resumed in a fairly strong Maiden with a plugging fifth over 1280m at Muswellbrook. Tackles an easier contest and stays in the mix.
